	<Title>
		Recipe: Gazpacho with garbanzo beans
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Gazpacho with garbanzo beans &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		6
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; The variation on this traditional cold Spanish soup adds garbanzo beans, which more than doubles the fiber content &amp;mdash; 4 grams fiber without, 9 grams fiber with the added garbanzo beans. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
In a large bowl, add the beans, vegetable juice, tomatoes, cucumber, onion, cilantro, hot pepper sauce, garlic and lime juice. Stir well. Cover and place in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or until well chilled. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
To serve, ladle the cold soup into chilled individual bowls and garnish with a lime wedge. Serve immediately. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 can (15 ounces) garbanzo beans, rinsed and drained&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;6 cups unsalted vegetable juice&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 cup cherry tomatoes, quartered&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup chopped, seeded cucumber&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup chopped red onion&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro or parsley&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 teaspoon hot pepper sauce&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 to 3 garlic cloves, minced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup lime juice&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;6 lime wedges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
